        -:   39://! The default null handling is NULL in, NULL out
        -:   40:enum class FunctionNullHandling : uint8_t { DEFAULT_NULL_HANDLING = 0, SPECIAL_HANDLING = 1 };
        -:   41://! The stability of the function, used by the optimizer
        -:   42://! CONSISTENT              -> this function always returns the same result when given the same input, no variance
        -:   43://! CONSISTENT_WITHIN_QUERY -> this function returns the same result WITHIN the same query/transaction
        -:   44://!                            but the result might change across queries (e.g. NOW(), CURRENT_TIME)
        -:   45://! VOLATILE                -> the result of this function might change per row (e.g. RANDOM())
        -:   46:enum class FunctionStability : uint8_t { CONSISTENT = 0, VOLATILE = 1, CONSISTENT_WITHIN_QUERY = 2 };
        -:   47:
        -:   48://! How to handle collations
        -:   49://! PROPAGATE_COLLATIONS        -> this function combines collation from its inputs and emits them again (default)
        -:   50://! PUSH_COMBINABLE_COLLATIONS  -> combinable collations are executed for the input arguments
        -:   51://! IGNORE_COLLATIONS           -> collations are completely ignored by the function
        -:   52:enum class FunctionCollationHandling : uint8_t {
        -:   53:	PROPAGATE_COLLATIONS = 0,
        -:   54:	PUSH_COMBINABLE_COLLATIONS = 1,
